            {
              "message": "T004 narrows active-doc cleanup to `knowledge/DESIGN.md`, while T001 deletes the whole `knowledge/strategy/` directory. Active docs named by the plan, including `CLAUDE.md` and `README.md`, still reference `knowledge/strategy/TODO-PLAN.md`; no task or AC covers those refs, so executing this plan leaves dead references despite the summary promising updates to all deleted paths.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/knowledge-strategy-cleanup-2026-06-17/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 21,
              "category": "contradiction"
            },
            {
              "message": "IN-03 describes both `knowledge/schemas/` files as `(auto-mode-*)`, but the plan's own T002 names `auto-state-schema.md` as one of the two targets. That pattern excludes one target file and makes the schema-deletion scope internally inconsistent.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/knowledge-strategy-cleanup-2026-06-17/spec.json",
